00:35.520 --> 00:41.760
a species that has an obligation to help save the planet, the biodiversity, the ecosystems

00:41.760 --> 00:43.260
and nature.

00:43.260 --> 00:50.160
Nature is calling out to us to open up our eyes to our responsibility as Earth citizens

00:50.160 --> 00:55.160
to be responsible in protecting the commons.

00:55.160 --> 01:02.240
And unfortunately, because of capitalism, religion, you know, all sorts of other factors,

01:02.240 --> 01:10.640
our vision has become so narrowed for just self-indulgence, self-profiteering.

01:10.640 --> 01:19.320
And the understanding of sharing for the commons has unfortunately retreated in the priorities

01:19.320 --> 01:22.680
of many human activities.

01:22.680 --> 01:30.120
You know, I do believe in the principles of capitalism insofar that individuals should

01:30.120 --> 01:34.520
be rewarded for their extraordinary efforts.

01:34.520 --> 01:37.160
So you have to be incentivized.

01:37.160 --> 01:43.880
But once you are incentivized and you do get ahead, you have a very, I think a very strong

01:43.880 --> 01:49.400
obligation to help others who are in need, because I think the lessons of evolution is

01:49.400 --> 01:56.000
not the survival of the fittest, but the sharing of surplus beyond your own needs to help your

01:56.000 --> 02:00.520
neighbors and help others who are less advantaged.

02:00.520 --> 02:05.440
So the message that I'm getting from self-sabotten mushrooms is the important role that humans

02:05.440 --> 02:14.000
play today in being able to provide for the health of the ecosystem for everyone.

02:14.000 --> 02:18.760
The common phrase is that a rising tide raises all boats.

02:18.760 --> 02:22.080
